<p-->Three is a lucky number for Doyle Duke and Tony Miranda. <p></p>



<p>Both men are alive today thanks to an extremely rare and complex surgery – a triple-organ transplant, including a heart, liver and kidney simultaneously.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miran-and-Doyle-Duke-16x9-1-1024x577.jpg" alt="Tony Miran and Doyle Duke-" class="wp-image-410253" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miran-and-Doyle-Duke-16x9-1-1024x577.jpg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miran-and-Doyle-Duke-16x9-1-300x169.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miran-and-Doyle-Duke-16x9-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miran-and-Doyle-Duke-16x9-1.jpg 1087w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Doyle Duke and Tony Miranda, triple-organ transplant patients</strong></figcaption></figure>



<p><strong><a href="https://youtu.be/PWEFgFy-BcU" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Watch: Rare transplant turns strangers into friends</a></strong></p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<div class="fluidEmbed"><iframe loading="lazy" id="videoidhttpsyoutubedEBcZR997Q" title="Rare transplant turns strangers into friends" width="500" height="281" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/dEB-cZR997Q?feature=oembed&amp;enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div>
</div></figure>



<p><strong>Journalists: Broadcast-quality video (1:52) is in the downloads at the end of this post. Please courtesy: "Mayo Clinic News Network." Read the&nbsp;<a href="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/FINAL-SCRIPT_Triple-transplant-patient-pkg-script___32.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">script</a>.</strong></p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Tony's story</strong></h2>



<p>Tony had always considered himself a healthy guy. You'd often find him out on the basketball court, playing with family and friends or just shooting hoops by himself.</p>



<p>Then, at 50 years old, Tony had to stop playing basketball. He was diagnosed with <a href="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/tag/congestive-heart-failure/" id="423052" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">congestive heart failure.</a> Over the next decade, Tony underwent one procedure after another. Still, his health continued to decline. </p>



<p>Doctors told Tony there was only one option left – a triple-organ transplant, including a heart, liver and kidney. The transplant is so rare and complex that it is performed at only a limited number of hospitals.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-in-hospital-prior-to-surgery-1024x576.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-410388" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-in-hospital-prior-to-surgery-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-in-hospital-prior-to-surgery-300x169.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-in-hospital-prior-to-surgery-768x432.jpg 768w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-in-hospital-prior-to-surgery-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-in-hospital-prior-to-surgery.jpg 1920w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Photo courtesy: Miranda family</strong></figcaption></figure>



<p>Tony turned to <a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/arizona?customer_id=919-955-2329&amp;mc_id=google&amp;campaign=51736151&amp;geo=9030072&amp;kw=mayo%20clinic%20arizona&amp;ad=458309050044&amp;network=g&amp;sitetarget=&amp;adgroup=112957983571&amp;extension=&amp;target=kwd-885409230&amp;matchtype=e&amp;device=c&amp;account=9199552329&amp;invsrc=arizona&amp;placementsite=arizona&amp;gad_source=1&amp;gad_campaignid=51736151&amp;gbraid=0AAAAAD8Qu2-PBFgfbrk-eT4yX_PVDq4CG&amp;gclid=CjwKCAiAqKbMBhBmEiwAZ3UboN8Dz0Z5DdxxmPBqpEPA8tbTvRf_LIVX4X5t2KDNnmhr7XML3w7inhoCx4MQAvD_BwE" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Mayo Clinic in Arizona</a>, where he found hope and a friend who would become his inspiration.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Hope comes calling</strong></h2>



<p>In 2025, Tony was admitted to Mayo Clinic. On the day of his triple-organ transplant, just hours before his surgery, Tony got an unexpected phone call.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miranda-on-phone-smile-1024x576.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-410210" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miranda-on-phone-smile-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miranda-on-phone-smile-300x169.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miranda-on-phone-smile-768x432.jpg 768w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miranda-on-phone-smile-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miranda-on-phone-smile.jpg 1920w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Tony speaking with Doyle before Tony's surgery</strong></figcaption></figure>



<p>"You're going to be just fine. You've got the best doctors and nurses," said Doyle, who was speaking from firsthand experience.  <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O0Po7Db_VCE" id="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O0Po7Db_VCE" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Doyle is Arizona's first patient to undergo a triple-organ transplant</a>, including a heart, liver and kidney.</p>



<p>Doyle called Tony to offer support and encouragement.</p>



<p>"You're going to feel a hundred percent better than you do today. I hurt, but I could tell a difference immediately," said Doyle, calling from his home in Pauls Valley, Oklahoma. In 2022, Doyle traveled with his wife Billie to Arizona to undergo the milestone triple-organ transplant.</p>



<p>The phone call was just what Tony needed to hear.</p>



<p>"It helped a lot talking to somebody who has gone through what I was going through," says Tony. "Every day I thought if Doyle did it, I can too. He was my inspiration."</p>



<p>Billie also spoke with Carrie, Tony's wife, to share her insight on being a caregiver. "She told me I could call her 24 hours a day," says Carrie. "I called her quite a bit. It was so helpful to speak with someone who had already been through this."</p>



<p>The families stayed in close contact throughout Tony's transplant journey.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="1024" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Doyle-Duke-spouse-1x1-1-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-410247" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Doyle-Duke-spouse-1x1-1-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Doyle-Duke-spouse-1x1-1-300x300.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Doyle-Duke-spouse-1x1-1-150x150.jpg 150w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Doyle-Duke-spouse-1x1-1-768x768.jpg 768w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Doyle-Duke-spouse-1x1-1.jpg 1359w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Billie and Doyle Duke three years after Doyle's triple-organ transplant</strong></figcaption></figure>



<p>Even though the two men had never met, Doyle says he didn't think twice about reaching out to Tony.</p>



<p>"Calling Tony was the least I could do to help Tony to understand what he's going to do and what he's got to do," says Doyle.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Mayo Clinic – a leader in triple-organ transplantation</strong></h2>



<p>Mayo Clinic also performs triple-organ transplants in <a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/patient-visitor-guide/minnesota" id="https://www.mayoclinic.org/patient-visitor-guide/minnesota" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Rochester, Minnesota</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miranda-Heart-Surgery-1-1024x576.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-410334" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miranda-Heart-Surgery-1-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miranda-Heart-Surgery-1-300x169.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miranda-Heart-Surgery-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miranda-Heart-Surgery-1-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Miranda-Heart-Surgery-1.jpg 1920w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure>



<p>As of February 2026, Mayo Clinic has performed 13 triple-organ transplants, according to the Organ Procurement and Transplantation Network.</p>



<p>In 2024, Mayo Clinic in Rochester performed a highly complex and rare triple transplant, including a heart, lungs and kidney.</p>



<p>The patient, Mike Loven, had battled serious health problems since childhood. He had three open-heart surgeries by the time he reached his teens. Mike lives in Coon Rapids, Minnesota with his wife and two daughters.</p>



<p>Like Tony and Doyle, doctors told Mike a triple-organ transplant was his only chance for survival.</p>



<p>The triple transplant was a success. "I'm feeling better than I have in years," says Mike. "I'm walking up to two miles on the treadmill. I'm back to working. I feel great."</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="955" height="955" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Mark-Loven-LifeSource-1x1-1.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-410246" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Mark-Loven-LifeSource-1x1-1.jpg 955w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Mark-Loven-LifeSource-1x1-1-300x300.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Mark-Loven-LifeSource-1x1-1-150x150.jpg 150w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Mark-Loven-LifeSource-1x1-1-768x768.jpg 768w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 955px) 100vw, 955px"><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>The Loven family works together to raise awareness about organ donation                                                   Photo courtesy: Loven family</strong></figcaption></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>Strangers no more</strong></h2>



<p>It's been nine months since Tony's triple-organ transplant. Doctors still closely monitor his progress, but he's back at home, enjoying time with family and friends.</p>



<p>Tony is even slowly making his way back to the basketball court.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-plays-ball-with-kids-1024x576.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-410403" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-plays-ball-with-kids-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-plays-ball-with-kids-300x169.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-plays-ball-with-kids-768x432.jpg 768w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-plays-ball-with-kids-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-plays-ball-with-kids.jpg 1920w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Tony with his grandchildren nine months after his triple-organ transplant</strong></figcaption></figure>



<p>Doyle and Billie made a special trip Arizona to meet their new friends in person.</p>



<p>"We share such a special bond," says Billie. "I know we'll be friends forever."</p>



<p>Though Mike has not met Tony and Doyle, the three begin each new day the same way – with deep gratitude for the <a href="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/discussion/expert-alert-5-reasons-to-consider-becoming-an-organ-donor/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">gift of life</a>.</p>



<p>"I hear my heart beat everyday and remember my donor, I'm so grateful. Thank you to my donor and donor family," says Tony. "Every day is a miracle day."</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Carrie-Doyle-and-Billie-1024x576.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-410335" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Carrie-Doyle-and-Billie-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Carrie-Doyle-and-Billie-300x169.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Carrie-Doyle-and-Billie-768x432.jpg 768w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Carrie-Doyle-and-Billie-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/02/Tony-Carrie-Doyle-and-Billie.jpg 1920w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"><figcaption class="wp-element-caption"><strong>Tony, Carrie, Doyle and Billie during their visit in Arizona</strong></figcaption></figure>



